3. Medicare Part D Big Data Pipeline (ETVL)

Built an end-to-end PySpark data pipeline to extract, transform, validate, and load large-scale government healthcare data to analyze prescription drug spending.

Skills demonstrated:

    Apache Spark (PySpark) & Distributed Computing

    Data Engineering Architecture (Medallion: Bronze, Silver, Gold)

    Infrastructure Debugging (JVM/Java side-loading in JupyterHub)

    Data Quality Validation & Schema Enforcement

    Big Data File Optimization (Parquet format)

Project Overview
This project processes a subset of the official CMS Medicare Part D Prescribers dataset. It takes a heavy, 84-column raw CSV file and transforms it through a multi-stage pipeline into a streamlined, highly compressed analytical report. By aggregating the data geographically, the pipeline quickly identifies which U.S. cities account for the highest total Medicare drug costs.

Business Problem
Healthcare organizations, insurers, and analysts need to track where Medicare dollars are being spent. However, raw government datasets are often too massive, noisy, and memory-intensive for standard tools like Excel or Pandas to handle efficiently. This pipeline automates the ingestion and cleaning of that data, turning a "Big Data" problem into instant, actionable geographic insights without crashing local environments.

Core Output (The "Gold" Layer)
Aggregated Geographic Spend Report:

    total_city_spend: Sum of all prescription drug costs for that city.

    doctor_count: The number of unique prescribing providers in that city.

Data Source & Features Extracted

    Source: Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services (CMS) Part D Prescribers Dataset.

    Extracted Features:

        Prscrbr_NPI (National Provider Identifier)

        Prscrbr_Last_Org_Name (Provider Name)

        Prscrbr_City (Geographic Location)

        Tot_Clms (Total Claim Count)

        Tot_Drug_Cst (Total Drug Cost)

Architecture & Tools

    Framework: PySpark

    Design Pattern: Medallion Architecture (Bronze: Raw Extraction -> Silver: Cleaned & Filtered -> Gold: Aggregated Business Logic)

    Storage Output: Apache Parquet (Optimized columnar storage)

    Environment: JupyterHub (with manual Java 11 environment variable configuration)

Validation Metrics (ETVL Pipeline)

    Pre-cleaning raw row & column ingestion audits.

    Null and duplicate record tracking.

    Automated data type casting (String to Integer/Double conversions).
